title: Pilot
description: Former FBI profiler Frank Black returns to his hometown of Seattle with his wife, Catherine, and his daughter, Jordan. Frank, the Seattle Police, and the mysterious Millennium Group investigate a series of sexual homicides being committed by a prophecy driven serial killer.

title: Gehenna
description: Frank investigates a doomsday cult and its powerful leader.

title: Dead Letters
description: Frank teams with with a troubled profiler and candidate for the Millennium Group named Jim Horn in order catch a dangerous killer.

title: The Judge
description: Frank Black is called in to investigate a murderer who is removing body parts and seemingly mailing them to random address. When Frank begins his investigation, he begins to realize that there may be more than one power involved.
Frank and Peter head to Washington in order to help the FBI investigate a serial bomber.

title: Kingdom Come
description: Frank investigates a serial killer who seems to be targeting the clergy.

title: Blood Relatives
description: Frank investigates a troubled orphan who may behind a number of murders at funerals.

title: The Well-Worn Lock
description: Catherine helps a victim of incest take her father to criminal court.

title: Wide Open
description: Frank tries to catch a killer who is targeting families with expensive security systems.

title: The Wild and the Innocent
description: Frank tries to find a girl and her murderous boyfriend who are looking for a baby that the girl's father forced her to give away.

title: Weeds
description: Frank investigates a series of abductions in a small designed neighborhood. The abductor is forcing his victims to pay for the sins of their fathers.

title: Loin Like a Hunting Flame
description: A pharmacist drugs unsuspecting couples and forces them to enact his sexual fantasies.

title: Force Majeure
description: The Millennium Group investigates the suicides of identical-twin girls born seven years apart.

title: The Thin White Line
description: Frank links two seemingly unrelated murders to the modus operandi of a serial killer who has been incarcerated for twenty years.

title: Sacrament
description: When his sister-in-law is kidnapped at her child's baptism, Frank must calm his brother and find the kidnapper before it is too late.

title: Covenant
description: Frank is asked to develop a psychological profile on a sheriff who confessed to murdering his entire family.

title: Walkabout
description: After walking up in an alley with amnesia, Frank has the bad feeling that someone has been murdered.

title: Lamentation
description: As Frank assists the FBI with the hunt for an escaped serial killer, an unspeakable evil terrorizes his family.

title: Powers, Principalities, Thrones and Dominions
description: Frank and the Millennium Group investigate a series of Satanic murders.

title: Broken World
description: Frank hunts down a serial-killer-in-the-making who takes pleasure in slaughtering horses.

title: Maranatha
description: Frank and Peter try to catch a Russian murderer with links to Chernobyl. In there search they discover a chilling information with apocalyptic ramifications.

title: Paper Dove
description: Frank attempts to clear the name of a man who may have been mistakenly convicted of murdering his wife.

title: The Beginning and the End
description: Frank comes into contact with the man who has been photographing his family.

title: Beware of the Dog
description: Frank investigates a number of dog-attacks in a sleepy town in Montana.

title: Sense and Antisense
description: Frank and the Millennium Group search for a man who may be infected with a terrible disease.

title: Monster
description: Frank investigates the owner of a daycare centre accused of committing child abuse - only to find himself at the centre of a similar investigation.

title: A Single Blade of Grass
description: Frank joins forces with an archeologist when the body of a recently-murdered Native American man is discovered amongst ancient remains.

title: The Curse of Frank Black
description: On Halloween night, Frank is haunted by the ghosts of memories past.
Frank and Watts join the search for a busload of missing children.

title: The Hand of Saint Sebastian
description: Frank and Watts travel to Germany where they seek a legendary holy relic.

title: Jose Chung's 'Doomsday Defense'
description: Novelist Jose Chung authors a short story critical of a millennial self-help movement and performs some profiling of his own when a college professor is found murdered.

title: Midnight of the Century
description: As Christmas approaches, Frank experiences visions from his childhood when Jordan claims to have been visited by the spirit of her dead grandmother.

title: Goodbye Charlie
description: A former doctor assists the terminally ill by helping them commit suicide. But is his motivation mercy... or murder?

title: Luminary
description: Frank searches for a young man who disappeared in the Alaskan wilderness.

title: The Mikado
description: A serial killer uses the Internet as a medium for broadcasting his victims' murders.

title: The Pest House
description: Asylum inmates become prime suspects in a series of murders linked to urban legend.

title: Owls
description: The discovery of the remains of the crucifixion cross threatens to divide the Millennium Group.

title: Roosters
description: As the schism between the two waring Millennium Group factions deepens, Frank discovers the existence of yet another player in the power struggle.

title: Siren
description: A mysterious Asian women is linked to several strange deaths aboard a ship.

title: In Arcadia Ego
description: Frank searches for a female serial killer and her lover after the pair escape from prison.

title: Anamnesis
description: Catherine and Lara investigate when five girls claim they saw a vision of the Virgin Mary.

title: A Room with No View
description: Frank senses that Bletcher's killer is responsible for the disappearance of a teenage boy.

title: Somehow, Satan Got Behind Me
description: Four devils gather at a donut shop and swap stories about their dealings with mankind.

title: The Fourth Horseman
description: Frank and Watts are quarantined after they come in contact with an unknown pathogen; Jordan experiences a terrifying nightmare; Lara Means disappears.

title: The Time Is Now
description: Frank learns more about a deadly virus sweeping across the land.
